    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-01T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.24/538: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-01T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 1, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 2—3:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>946. United Press reports appearing in Colombian press May 31 quotes Hector Lazo
                    of the Board of Economic Warfare<note n="12" xml:id="d171fn12">Assistant
                        Director in charge of the Office of Exports.</note> as stating that the
                    Decentralization Plan will be applied in the future only on articles subject to
                    control by War Production Board. Please telegraph urgently whether this
                    statement is true as the effect on the local certifying agency of this
                    unconfirmed report is further to delay the issuance of Import
                    Recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
